==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Notoriety
<hw>No`to*ri"e*ty</hw> <pr>(n⟦omac⟧`t⟦osl⟧*r⟦imac⟧"⟦esl⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>notori⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Notorious</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or condition of being
notorious; the state of being generally or publicly known; -- commonly
used in an unfavorable sense; <as>as, the <ex>notoriety</ex> of a
crime</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were not subjects in their own nature so exposed to public
<qex>notoriety</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notorious</ent>⟦br⟧
